title SIE GSM â€” ElementDefinition Lifecycle - v1.0.0

note as Legend
  This diagram is the lifecycle state machine of the GSM
  `ElementDefinition`.

  **Status Semantics**:

  - DRAFT: initial creation state. Editable authoring state; not in effect at
    runtime.
  - PROPOSED: submitted for review. Under governance review; not in effect at
    runtime.
  - APPROVED: accepted as a valid definition; version assigned. Awaiting
    activation; not yet in effect.
  - ACTIVE: in effect at runtime.
  - SUSPENDED: temporarily not in effect, retains lineage; may be reactivated.
  - DEPRECATED: in effect but scheduled for retirement; emits warnings on new
    references.
  - RETIRED: permanently not in effect; preserved for historical traceability
    (terminal).
  - REJECTED: denied; not in effect. A new creative cycle requires authoring a
    new revision (terminal).
end note

note as Coupling
  **Element Lifecycle Coupling Rules (per element)**

  Two kinds of edges between elements:

  "Composition" = parent owns child, cascade on
  transition:
    Structureâ†’Mechanism/Interaction/Interface,
    Mechanismâ†’Effector/Receptor,
    Effectorâ†’Artifact (emits).

  "Reference" = independent elements, ordering
  constraint:
    Interactionâ†’Effector (from),
    Interactionâ†’Receptor (to),
    Interfaceâ†’Effector/Receptor (exposes),
    Receptorâ†’Artifact (receives).

  Progress path (maturity scale):
  DRAFT < PROPOSED < APPROVED < ACTIVE/SUSPENDED.
  ACTIVE and SUSPENDED are the same maturity level.
  DEPRECATED, RETIRED, REJECTED are off this scale.

  ====

  **When a Structure transitions:**

  Progress (DRAFTâ†’PROPOSEDâ†’APPROVEDâ†’ACTIVE):
  - Cascade: all constituents advance to the same
    status. If any constituent cannot make that
    transition, the Structure's transition is rejected.
  - No constituent may be further along the progress
    path than the Structure.
  - Lagging constituents are allowed while Structure
    is ACTIVE.

  Suspension (ACTIVE/DEPRECATEDâ†”SUSPENDED):
  - Cascade: only ACTIVE, SUSPENDED, and DEPRECATED
    constituents are toggled to SUSPENDED (or back).
  - DRAFT, PROPOSED, APPROVED constituents stay where
    they are (they are not in-effect, suspension is
    irrelevant to them).
  - RETIRED, REJECTED constituents stay where they are
    (terminal, no transitions possible).
  - On un-suspension, each constituent is restored to
    its pre-suspension status (ACTIVE or DEPRECATED),
    derived from the audit trail.

  Decommission (â†’DEPRECATEDâ†’RETIRED):
  - Precondition: all constituents must already be
    DEPRECATED or RETIRED.
  - Cascade: all constituents advance to the same
    status.

  Rejection (PROPOSEDâ†’REJECTED):
  - Cascade: only PROPOSED constituents are rejected.
  - DRAFT constituents stay DRAFT (they were never
    submitted for governance review, they cannot be
    "rejected").

  ====

  **When a Mechanism transitions:**

  All paths (uniform):
  - Cascade: all its Effectors and Receptors advance to
    the same status (strict equality).
  - The Mechanism can only transition if all its ports
    can follow.

  ====

  **When an Effector transitions:**

  All paths (uniform):
  - Cascade: its emitted Artifact advances to the same
    status (strict equality).
  - The Effector can only transition if its Artifact
    can follow.

  Progress:
  - No condition from Interactions originating from
    this Effector. The Effector is the "upstream" side
    of the reference: advancing it only widens the gap
    with the Interaction. No check needed.
  - No condition from Interfaces exposing this
    Effector. The port is the "upstream" side: advancing
    it only widens the gap with the Interface. No check
    needed.

  Suspension (ACTIVE/DEPRECATEDâ†”SUSPENDED):
  - Composition cascade to the emitted Artifact still
    applies (see "All paths" above).
  - No reference-edge checks on Interactions or
    Interfaces: ACTIVE and SUSPENDED are the same
    maturity level â€” toggling between them cannot
    create an ordering violation.
  - Mechanismâ†’Effector (parentâ†’child): no constraint.
    The Effector is cascaded BY its owning Mechanism,
    not the other way around.

  Decommission/Rejection:
  - Existing Interactions from this Effector remain
    valid (frozen/inert).
  - No new Interactions may originate from a
    DEPRECATED, RETIRED, or REJECTED Effector.

  ====

  **When a Receptor transitions:**

  No cascade (Receptor composes nothing).

  Progress:
  - The Artifact this Receptor receives must already be
    at the target status or further along the progress
    path (DRAFT < PROPOSED < APPROVED < ACTIVE/SUSPENDED).
    If the Artifact is DEPRECATED, RETIRED, or REJECTED,
    the check is satisfied â€” it already went through
    ACTIVE.
  - Every Interaction targeting this Receptor must
    already be at the target status or further along the
    progress path. If the Interaction is DEPRECATED,
    RETIRED, or REJECTED, the check is satisfied.
  - No new Receptorâ†’Artifact bindings to DEPRECATED,
    RETIRED, or REJECTED Artifacts.

  Suspension (ACTIVE/DEPRECATEDâ†”SUSPENDED):
  - No reference-edge checks on the received Artifact
    or on Interactions targeting this Receptor: ACTIVE
    and SUSPENDED are the same maturity level â€”
    toggling between them cannot create an ordering
    violation.
  - Mechanismâ†’Receptor (parentâ†’child): no constraint.
    The Receptor is cascaded BY its owning Mechanism,
    not the other way around.

  Decommission/Rejection:
  - Existing Receptorâ†’Artifact bindings remain valid
    (frozen/inert).
  - No new Receptorâ†’Artifact bindings to DEPRECATED,
    RETIRED, or REJECTED Artifacts.

  ====

  **When an Interaction transitions:**

  No cascade (Interaction composes nothing).

  Progress:
  - The Effector this Interaction originates from must
    already be at the target status or further along
    the progress path. If the Effector is DEPRECATED,
    RETIRED, or REJECTED, the check is satisfied â€” it
    already went through ACTIVE.
  - No precondition from the Receptor it targets.
    The Interaction is the "upstream" side: advancing it
    only widens the gap with the Receptor. No check
    needed.

  Suspension (ACTIVE/DEPRECATEDâ†”SUSPENDED):
  - No reference-edge checks on the Effector or
    Receptor this Interaction references: ACTIVE and
    SUSPENDED are the same maturity level â€” toggling
    between them cannot create an ordering violation.
  - Structureâ†’Interaction (parentâ†’child): no
    constraint. The Interaction is cascaded BY its
    owning Structure, not the other way around.

  Decommission/Rejection:
  - The Effector-side Structure decommissions first
    (since the Interaction is owned by the Effector-side
    Structure).
  - Existing references to Effector and Receptor remain
    valid (frozen/inert).
  - No new Interactions may be created targeting
    DEPRECATED, RETIRED, or REJECTED elements.

  ====

  **When an Interface transitions:**

  No cascade (Interface composes nothing).

  Progress:
  - Every port (Effector or Receptor) this Interface
    exposes must already be at the target status or
    further along the progress path. If a port is
    DEPRECATED, RETIRED, or REJECTED, the check is
    satisfied â€” it already went through ACTIVE.

  Suspension (ACTIVE/DEPRECATEDâ†”SUSPENDED):
  - No reference-edge checks on the exposed ports:
    ACTIVE and SUSPENDED are the same maturity level â€”
    toggling between them cannot create an ordering
    violation.
  - Structureâ†’Interface (parentâ†’child): no constraint.
    The Interface is cascaded BY its owning Structure,
    not the other way around.

  Decommission/Rejection:
  - Existing exposure remains valid (frozen/inert).
  - No new exposure of DEPRECATED, RETIRED, or REJECTED
    ports.

  ====

  **When an Artifact transitions:**

  Artifact is normally cascaded by its emitting Effector.
  When also received by Receptors, those Receptors are
  not affected (no cascade upward).

  Progress:
  - No precondition from Receptors that receive this
    Artifact. The Artifact is the "upstream" side:
    advancing it only widens the gap with the Receptor.
    No check needed.

  Suspension (ACTIVE/DEPRECATEDâ†”SUSPENDED):
  - No reference-edge checks on Receptors that receive
    this Artifact: ACTIVE and SUSPENDED are the same
    maturity level â€” toggling between them cannot
    create an ordering violation.
  - Effectorâ†’Artifact (parentâ†’child): no constraint.
    The Artifact is cascaded BY its emitting Effector,
    not the other way around.

  Decommission/Rejection:
  - Existing Receptorâ†’Artifact bindings remain valid
    (frozen/inert).
  - No new Receptorâ†’Artifact bindings may target a
    DEPRECATED, RETIRED, or REJECTED Artifact.
end note

note as AuditRules
  **Audit-log invariants (ElementDefinitionStatusTransition)**

  - Transitions are append-only; never modify/delete.
  - The first transition represents creation:
    `preStatus = null`, `postStatus = DRAFT`.
  - Transition timestamps are monotonic:
    each `datetime` is >= the preceding `datetime`.
  - The current `status` is derived/denormalized from the
    latest transition's `postStatus`.
  - Terminality: once `status` is REJECTED or RETIRED, no
    additional transitions may be appended.
end note

state "Qualification" as Qualification {
  state DRAFT
}

state "Review" as Review {
  state PROPOSED
  state APPROVED
}

state "Production" as Production {
  state ACTIVE
  state SUSPENDED
  state DEPRECATED
}

state "Terminal" as Terminal {
  state REJECTED
  state RETIRED
}

' ------------------------------------------------------------
' Progress Flow
' ------------------------------------------------------------

[*] -right-> DRAFT
DRAFT -right-> PROPOSED
PROPOSED -right-> APPROVED
APPROVED -right-> ACTIVE

' ------------------------------------------------------------
' Degress Flows
' ------------------------------------------------------------

SUSPENDED -up-> ACTIVE
ACTIVE -down-> SUSPENDED
DEPRECATED -down-> SUSPENDED
SUSPENDED -right-> DEPRECATED

DRAFT -down-> REJECTED
PROPOSED -down-> REJECTED
REJECTED --> [*]

ACTIVE -right-> DEPRECATED
DEPRECATED -right-> RETIRED
RETIRED --> [*]

